  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This trial seeks to investigate the feasibility and effectiveness of delivering a newly
      manualized family-based treatment for adolescents with anorexia nervosa
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This open trial seeks to investigate the feasibility and effectiveness of delivering a newly
      manualized family-based treatment for adolescents with anorexia nervosa at a site beyond the
      treatment's origin. Adolescents ages 12-17 with anorexia nervosa or subthreshold anorexia
      nervosa were treated with up to one year of this approach.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
